 {"id":"coding_agent_usage_tracker-6nx","title":"Budget: Implement timezone-aware reset scheduling","description":"## Summary
Handle budget period boundaries correctly with configurable timezone.

## The Problem
When does "daily" reset? Midnight in what timezone?

## Configuration
```toml
# ~/.config/caut/budgets.toml
[settings]
timezone = "America/New_York"  # Default: local system timezone
week_starts_on = "monday"      # monday or sunday

[claude]
monthly_limit = 75.00
# Month resets on 1st at midnight in configured timezone
```

## Implementation
```rust
pub struct BudgetPeriod {
    pub period_type: PeriodType,  // Daily, Weekly, Monthly
    pub timezone: Tz,
    pub week_start: Weekday,
}

impl BudgetPeriod {
    pub fn current_period_start(&self) -> DateTime<Tz> {
        let now = Utc::now().with_timezone(&self.timezone);
        match self.period_type {
            PeriodType::Daily => now.date().and_hms(0, 0, 0),
            PeriodType::Weekly => {
                let days_since_start = (now.weekday().num_days_from_monday() 
                    - self.week_start.num_days_from_monday() + 7) % 7;
                (now - Duration::days(days_since_start as i64)).date().and_hms(0, 0, 0)
            }
            PeriodType::Monthly => {
                now.date().with_day(1).unwrap().and_hms(0, 0, 0)
            }
        }
    }

